view.name: MTA Subway Stations
view.description: A dataset listing all subway and Staten Island Railway stations, with information on their locations, Station Master Reference Number (MRN), Complex MRN, GTFS Stop ID, the services that stop there, the type of structure the station is on or in, whether the station is in Manhattanâ€™s Central Business District (CBD), and their ADA-accessibility status.

columns.name: GTFS Stop ID
columns.description: The ID used for the station in the General Transit Feed Specification (GTFS), an open standard used to display public transit schedule data.

columns.name: Station ID
columns.description: The Station Master Reference Number.

columns.name: Complex ID
columns.description: The Complex Master Reference Number.

columns.name: Division
columns.description: The division of the subway system (IRT, BMT, or IND) that the station is a part of.

columns.name: Line
columns.description: The operational line of the subway system the station is located on, such as Queens Blvd, Lexington Av, or Sea Beach.

columns.name: Stop Name
columns.description: The name of the subway station.

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: The borough the station is in. Bx for Bronx, B for Brooklyn, M for Manhattan, Q for Queens, SI for Staten Island.

columns.name: CBD
columns.description: This indicates whether or not a station is in Manhattanâ€™s Central Business District (CBD). This value is either TRUE or FALSE.

columns.name: Daytime Routes
columns.description: The subway routes that serve the station during weekdays.

columns.name: Structure
columns.description: The type of structure the subway station is located on or in (At Grade, Elevated, Embankment, Open Cut, Subway, Viaduct, etc.). For stations part of a complex, this indicates the construction type for that part of the complex only. Some complexes have more than one construction type across their constituent stations.

columns.name: GTFS Latitude
columns.description: The latitude for the centroid of the station

columns.name: GTFS Longitude
columns.description: The longitude for the centroid of the station

columns.name: North Direction Label
columns.description: The northbound direction for lines stopping at the station, such as Astoria - Ditmars Blvd, Uptown & The Bronx, and Manhattan. This is blank if the station is the northern terminal of a line.

columns.name: South Direction Label
columns.description: The southbound direction for lines stopping at the station, such as Downtown & Brooklyn, Canarsie - Rockaway Parkway, and Brighton Beach & Coney Island. This is blank if the station is the southern terminal of a line.

columns.name: ADA
columns.description: 0 if the station is not ADA-accessible, 1 if the station is fully accessible, 2 if the station is partially accessible.

columns.name: ADA Northbound
columns.description: 0 if the station is not ADA-accessible in the northbound direction, 1 if the station is fully accessible in the northbound direction

columns.name: ADA Southbound
columns.description: 0 if the station is not ADA-accessible in the southbound direction, 1 if the station is fully accessible in the southbound direction

columns.name: ADA Notes
columns.description: Notes on the direction a station is accessible in if it is only accessible in one direction, such as Manhattan-bound only, Downtown only, and Uptown & The Bronx local only.

columns.name: Georeference
columns.description: Open Data platform-generated geocoding information from supplied address components. Point-type location is the centroid of the address components provided and does not reflect a specific address if the street address component is not provided. Point-type location is supplied in "POINT (<geocoded longitude> <geocoded latitude>)" format.

columns.name: NYS Municipal Boundaries
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset 'NYS Municipal Boundaries' (yamh-8v7k) the point in column 'georeference' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.

columns.name: New York Zip Codes
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset 'New York Zip Codes' (wbg7-3whc) the point in column 'georeference' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.

columns.name: Counties
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset 'Counties' (kjdx-g34t) the point in column 'georeference' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.
